problem:
Two circles are centered at the origin, as shown.  The point $P(99,20)$ is on the larger circle and the point $S(0,k)$ is on the smaller circle.  If $QR=50$, what is the value of $k$? [asy]
defaultpen(linewidth(.7pt)+fontsize(10pt));
dotfactor=4;
draw(Circle((0,0),51)); draw(Circle((0,0),101));
dot((0,0)); dot((51,0)); dot((101,0)); dot((0,51)); dot((99,20));
draw((0,0)--(99,20));
label("$S (0,k)$",(0,7.5),W);
draw((104,0)--(0,0)--(0,104),Arrows(TeXHead));
draw((-104,0)--(0,0)--(0,-104));

label("$x$",(104,0),E); label("$y$",(0,104),N); label("$P(99,20)$",(99,20),NE);

label("$O$",(0,0),SW); label("$Q$",(51,0),SW); label("$R$",(101,0),SE);

[/asy]
